PROP - read-only properties that share between components.
Props (short for "properties") in React are the primary way to pass data from a parent component to a child component, making components reusable and dynamic.
Props (short for Properties) are used to pass data from a parent component to a child component.


PropTypes are used to check the type of props passed to a component.

Condition rendering - allow you to control what get rendered in your application based on certain condition (show,hide or change conponents)

click event -> An interaction when user click on any specific element. We can response to click by passing a callback to the onClick event handler

react-hook - special function that allow functional components to use react features without writing class components
React Hooks are functions that allow you to use state and other React features inside functional components.
A hook is just a special React function.

useState() - A react hook allows the creation of a stateful variable and a setter function to updates its value in the virtul 
useState is a React Hook that stores changing data in a component.

onchange - event handler used primarly with form elements ex.-> <input> , <textarea> , <select> , <radio>
onChange is an event that runs a function whenever the value of an input field changes.

Updater Function - A function passsed as an argument to setState() usually 
ex  (setYear + 1)
Allow for safe updates based on the previous state  